Content: The “de-risking” that some advocate is in actually synonymous with “de-cooperation”. Instead of reducing risks, it will only increase the risks, those of misunderstanding, distrust and error of judgment.
China and France are partners, not adversaries; they should cooperate more, rather than “decouple themselves”.
China and France must continue efforts to find common ground beyond differences, demonstrate inclusiveness towards each the other, and appreciate and strengthen each other.
A Chinese adage says, “ the things of the world can develop without rivalry, just as the four seasons alternate without contradiction.”
... and certainty to this tormented and uncertain world.

We must demonstrate lucidity and unfailing determination to unequivocally support multilateralism and economic globalization, and make them so that the solid development of Sino-French relations instills more factors of stability...

This is by always remaining faithful to the initial commitment made when the establishment of their diplomatic relations-“independence, mutual understanding, foresight, mutual benefit and “win-win”, that Sino-French relations have obtained the successes of 'Today.
Sino-French relations cannot, and above all must not, be dependent on, targeted against or restricted by a third party.
Sino-French relations have a pioneering and global character, they put at not only the well-being of the Chinese and French people, but also stability and development of the world.

Only by keeping up with the times and adhering to integrity and innovating can time-honored brands have more vitality. Recently, 55 brands have been removed from the list of Chinese time-honored brands. Delisting is both a spur and a reminder. Those time-honored brands that have stood out over time are probably in line with consumers' appetites in terms of taste and management, and have followed the trend of the times.

These products, which you can put in your shopping cart but can't buy, are very encouraging! Recently, an e-commerce shopping platform has launched 16 new "hard goods" that can only be seen but not bought, all of which have broken through the "stuck neck" "The core technology of the problem. This novel marketing has positive significance in boosting the confidence of all sectors of society in China's "smart" manufacturing and in deepening the public's understanding of the achievements of scientific researchers.

The Chinese government is firmly determined to protect its citizens. Recently, the Chinese public security publicly wanted four important leaders of a telecom fraud group in northern Myanmar. Some criminal groups in northern Myanmar have opened fraud dens for a long time, openly armed themselves to protect fraud, and are even suspected of intentional homicide, intentional injury, illegal detention and other serious violent crimes. They are extremely rampant. But no matter what difficulties and obstacles there may be, the Chinese government's determination to protect its citizens will not diminish.

How can Chinese time-honored brands shine with new glory? Recently, 55 brands with long-term poor management have been removed from the list of Chinese time-honored brands. To make time-honored brands evergreen, we must establish a mechanism for their healthy development. Reviewing time-honored brands and establishing an exit mechanism are part of this effort. Only by adhering to long-termism and relying on the quality of goods and services to win the trust of consumers can time-honored brands shine with new brilliance.

We must firmly adhere to the status of intergovernmental negotiations as the main channel for discussing security reform issues. Whether future summits will include security reform content and whether a consensus language can be reached must be determined by intergovernmental negotiations. China opposes "step-by-step" and "piecemeal handling" and opposes the attempt by a few countries to force the expansion of the "two categories" resolution at the UN General Assembly.

Ambassador Zhang Jun: The reform of the Security Council must anchor the root issues, adhere to the right direction, and effectively increase the representation and voice of developing countries. China has signed intergovernmental science and technology cooperation agreements with more than 80 Belt and Road Initiative co-building countries. Together, they have built more than 50 Belt and Road joint research laboratories in areas such as hygiene, transportation, materials and energy, as well as more than 20 agricultural technology demonstration centers and more than 70 overseas industrial parks.

The international science and technology cooperation initiative includes six specific contents, including respect for science, innovative development, openness and cooperation, equality and inclusion, unity and cooperation, and universal benefits and win-win. The establishment of a global scientific research fund and the expansion of science and technology support to developing countries are also being proposed. Click here for English version https://en.most.gov.cn/pressroom/202311/t20231107_188729.htm…

At the first "One Belt, One Road" science and technology exchange conference held the other day, the Chinese government proposed the first "international science and technology cooperation initiative." Based on the ideals of openness, fairness, fairness, and non-discrimination, we advocate ``Science has no borders and the benefits of science can be brought to all humanity,'' and we will build a global science and technology community together with the world.

China will continue to strengthen practical cooperation with Japan and South Korea, jointly lead to the success of important multilateral processes such as the 28th Conference of the Parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (COP28), the International Instrument on the Prevention of Plastic Pollution, and the United Nations Environment Conference. and intends to make new and even greater contributions to the sustainable development of the world.

Strengthening cooperation in environmental protection, green development of the region, and improvement of people's welfare are common aspirations of China, Japan, and South Korea. China has participated in international cooperation in the spirit of openness, inclusiveness and cooperation, and win-win, and has demonstrated leadership and achieved historic results in conserving biodiversity at COP15. The company also did not mention the incident of dragging pedestrians in subsequent reports. This resulted in the DMV not discovering the algorithm flaw until October 24, and suspending Cruise’s license to deploy autonomous vehicles and driverless testing. (3/4)

The driverless taxi braked suddenly after the collision, but after braking, the algorithm "decided to move the car to the side of the road in order to avoid blocking traffic" and rolled pedestrians under the car during the parking process. , dragged a full 6 meters. It was not until emergency personnel arrived at the scene with hydraulic pliers that the pedestrian was rescued and taken to the hospital. (2/4)
